  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Did not Solomon king of Israel sin by these things?.... By marrying strange wives, by whom he was drawn into idolatry, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 11:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "yet among many nations was there no king like him; as not for grandeur and riches, so not for wisdom, and yet was ensnared by his idolatrous wives: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "who was beloved of God; alluding to his name Jedidiah, which signifies beloved of the Lord, 2 Samuel 12:24 ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "who was beloved of God; alluding to his name Jedidiah, which signifies beloved of the Lord, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 12:24",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and God made him king over all Israel; which was a proof of his love to him, and so he was under the greater obligation to serve him, and him only, and yet his heart, through his wives, was turned after other gods: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "even him did outlandish women cause to sin; and if so great and wise a man was enticed by them to idolatry, much more may you, and therefore it was very dangerous to marry with them. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "even him did outlandish women cause to sin; and if so great and wise a man was enticed by them to idolatry, much more may you, and therefore it was very dangerous to marry with them. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
