  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 26.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Did not Solomon... sin by these things?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The example adduced was more apt than any other to move Jews. Israelites might have felt more deeply the case of Ahab (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 21:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Solomon's sin in \"going after strange wives,\" and its punishment, are set forth very fully in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 11:1-40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Among many nations there was no king like him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The reference is not so much to particular texts (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "e.g.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 3:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 1:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") as to the general description of Solomon, his glory, and his greatness (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 4-10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 1-9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".), which set him above all other earthly monarchs. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Who was beloved of his God",
        "children": []
